## 7. 🔄 Dry Run
```
insert(1): nums=[1],       map={1:0}
insert(2): nums=[1,2],     map={1:0, 2:1}
insert(3): nums=[1,2,3],   map={1:0, 2:1, 3:2}

remove(2):
  idx of 2 = 1
  last_val = 3 (nums[-1])
  nums[1] = 3  → nums=[1,3,3]
  map[3] = 1   → map={1:0, 3:1, 2:1}
  pop()        → nums=[1,3]
  del map[2]   → map={1:0, 3:1}
  ✓ Done!

getRandom(): picks from [1,3] → 50/50 chance
```

**Edge case — what if removing the LAST element itself?**
```
remove(3) when nums=[1,3], 3 is last:
  idx of 3 = 1 (which IS the last index)
  last_val = 3 (same element!)
  nums[1] = 3  (no change — self-swap)
  map[3] = 1   (no change)
  pop()        → nums=[1]
  del map[3]   → map={1:0}
  ✓ Works correctly!
```

