## 8. ⚠️ Common Mistakes Table

| Mistake | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Forgetting to update `last_val`'s index in map | `getRandom` lo wrong index → crash | Always do `map[last_val] = idx` |
| Not handling "removing the last element" edge case | Self-swap happens — it still works fine, but some get confused | Code handles it automatically ✓ |
| Using `list.remove(val)` instead of `list.pop()` | O(n) instead of O(1) | Always pop last, never remove by value |
| Returning wrong boolean | insert when exists → should return False | Check map first |
| Using `list.index(val)` for lookup | O(n) linear scan | Use HashMap instead |

